caption.p: Effect of different doses of C. osmophloeum ct. linalool leaf oil on motor coordination in ICR mice by the rotarod assay. Data are presented as mean ± S.D. ( n = 7); TH100: trazodone hydrochloride, 100 mg/Kg; LO100, LO200, and LO400: leaf oil, 100 mg/Kg, 200 mg/Kg, and 400 mg/Kg. Different letters (a–b) in the figure are significantly different at the level of p < 0.05 according to the Scheffe’s test.
